# Hustlr E-commerce Backend

A RESTful Product API for an e-commerce platform built with **Node.js**, **Express**, and **MongoDB**, following **Clean Architecture** principles with **CQRS** and **Dependency Injection** patterns.  
API is fully documented with **Swagger** for easy testing and exploration.

---

## **Features**
- Get all products
- Get a single product by ID
- Filter products by category (query parameter)
- Add new products with validation (optional bonus)
- MongoDB connection (local)
- Swagger API documentation

---

## **Architecture & Design Patterns**
- **Clean Architecture** for separation of concerns
- **CQRS** (Command Query Responsibility Segregation)
- **Dependency Injection** for easy testing and maintainability
- **Swagger** for API documentation

---

## **Tech Stack**
- **Node.js** (Runtime)
- **Express.js** (Web framework)
- **MongoDB + Mongoose** (Database & ODM)
- **Swagger** (API documentation)

---

## **Getting Started**

### **1. Clone the Repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ShakeelAhmadDev/hustlr-ecommerce-backend.git

move into the project directory

cd hustlr-ecommerce-backend

install packages

npm install 


then start project 
npm start 
